DISTANCE calculation:-¶

In [ ]:
lon1 = df['longitude_of_pickup']/57.29577951
lon2 = df['longitude_of_dropoff']/57.29577951
lat1 = df['latitude_of_pickup']/57.29577951
lat2 = df['latitude_of_dropoff']/57.29577951
      
dlon = lon2 - lon1
dlat = lat2 - lat1
a = np.sin(dlat / 2)**2 + (np.cos(lat1) * np.cos(lat2) * np.sin(dlon / 2))**2

c = 2 * np.arcsin(np.sqrt(a))
r = 6371
      
df['distance']=round(c * r, 2)

Checking dependency of fare amount on weekdays

In [36]:
amnt=[]
for i in range(0, 7):
    amnt.append(df[df.date_time_of_pickup.dt.weekday==i].amount.sum())
week=['sunday', 'monday', 'tuesday', 'wednesday', 'thursday', 'friday', 'saturday']
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 7))
plt.plot(week, amnt)
plt.show()

Amount collected diverges for different weekdays, least on saturday and highest on thursday.

In [37]:
#plotting in ascending order to allot integer values to weekdays in that order
